Place veggie burger on baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees F for 8 minutes. Turn burger. Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning. Bake at 350 degrees F for 7 to 8 minutes more or until heated through. Meanwhile, in small nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray, cook onion over medium-low heat about 5 minutes or until tender. Place lettuce leaf on bun bottom. Top with burger, tomato slice, onion rings, blue cheese and bun top. ON THE GRILL: Preheat grill. Use a food thermometer to be sure patties reach minimum internal temperature of 160 degrees F.